sentences: Yasmine Azaiez (born 16 October 1988) is a British-born violinist of Tunisian descent.
Yasmine began to play the violin when she was just four years old.
When Yasmine was eight years old, she was accepted into the Yehudi Menuhin School in Surrey, England.

She began performing on stage at around eleven years of age, and, when she was seventeen years old, she earned second place at the "Young Musician of the Year Competition" in Sevenoaks, Great Britain.
